-GL of SoY- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukaradin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NB-GM</span><br>  Posts: 245<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/16/02 12:46:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Problems in HoT</span><hr size=1> I will correct you, since yes, you're wrong.  The RTA is our community board.  It hashes out rules for the Planes (long since done).  It's where we rant and rave, and post links to boards with better rant sections than our own.  The RTA has *nothing* to do with creating Rotation rules, short of hosting a link to the list that tracks each mob and what guild is up for said mob.  The rules for any rotation are made among the guilds it affects - namely the guilds who kill any particular mob.  There is no reason that BOTS and TL should care what Noble Blade thinks about how the Blood of Ssra or High Priest rotations SHOULD be like; until we get on the rotation, its a non-issue.  Our input isn't needed and isn't given.  The same is true for every other rotation mob.  There is no reason for Guild X, Y, or Z to have input on a rotation that doesn't affect them.<br>
<br>
Any guild joining a rotation has the responsibility to find out what is involved.  The basics are posted (i.e. kill said mob on your own without assistance), and any minute details are relayed through simple tells to the guilds on the rotation (if any).  I find it odd that the same guilds who have NO qualms asking how many hp a mob has or what it AEs for can't be bothered to ask for the other details like &quot;Are the Named drakes FFA or part of the rotation?&quot;  It's an incredibly easy logical conclusion to anyone with a reading comprehension level above third grade: Half the Dozekar quest items come from him and the other Half from the Named drakes.  To claim &quot;I didn't know this might be an issue&quot; is to either be stupid or a liar.  <br>
<br>
LoM was responsible enough to ask (grats Xedd!), there is no reason other GMs can't be as responsible about making sure their guild doesn't violate the agreements of the rotations they are trying to become a part of.  It's not up to the Rotation guilds to keep tabs on all other guilds to find out who is doing HoT and get in touch with them.  We have more than enough to keep us busy with running guilds, making sure we don't break rules, killing rotation mobs, etc.  It's not Gradukk's, Emil's, Karadin's, Xedd's, Rogg's, etc's job to help you run your guild.  It's yours.<br>
<br>
For those of you who have your facts additionally *wrong* that the Named were never a part of the Dozekar rotation, Gradukk and I *created* the Dozekar rotation.  The Named were *always* part of it, and neither Tindi Losi nor Noble Blade *ever* stole Named from each other.<br>
<br>
Regardless, since the rules need to be put in black and white for people, they now have been.  However, this is NOT a change from how this rotation has always been.  The Named were always part of the Dozekar rotation, and we didn't have any trouble with it until the last 4-6 weeks.<br>
<br>
And for the last time, no, the door to HoT does not affect mob aggro from the hub.  That is one of three things: a KOS person standing too close to the mobs in the hub, a corpse drag too close to the hub mobs, or fighting HoT mobs too close to the hub mobs.  Whether the door is open or closed, they will still come in.  There was no gunman on the grassy gnoll (sic), there was no anti-camp code on the jboots in Najena, and there is no reason for the HoT door to be the focus of so much inquiry.  Continue to ask about the hub door all you want, but don't be surprised when people disregard your superstition. <p><p><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net"><img src="http://www.noble-blade.net/images/ezboard/sig-small.gif" align="left" border="0"></a>Karadin Firethorne<br>Assassin of The Rathe<br><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net">Noble Blade</a> 
